In terms of being mage VS wiz.<br>
B4 i start I will say all classes have thier place and all are = in power when it comes to doing the job they are assigned.<br>
<br>
That said.....  Mages are easier to level up between the levels of 4-29 than wizard.... however it's been my experience that 29-60 coes much faster on wizard than on mage solo being that I quad with my wizard ,... and when I am not quadding I wil just kite one mob and either way with KEI or c4 will have hardly no downtime.<br>
mages seem to be getting the edge in terms of DPS these days but wizards are more flashy.<br>
Wizards can port/evac and in some places at the lower levels (51-60) you will be awarded a group simply because you can port out is the poop hits the fan.<br>
Mages aren't very saught after for their damage as it seems until later levels (61+) even tho they do good damage well b4 then.<br>
Wizards cover a bigger range in ters of resists they nuke cold/magic/fire<br>
Mages only cover fire/magic.... and the water pet does cold but.....<br>
Mages have no defensive skill/escape other than gate and pet.<br>
Wizards have evac/snare/root/stun<br>
==============================================<br>
==============================================<br>
<br>
Moving on to partnering;<br>
Partnering with a mage :<br>
<br>
Shaman make awesome partner for mage.<br>
they have the ability to slow the mob... send in a pet of their own and heal your pet as well while doing some melee/dot damage as well.<br>
<br>
Cleric also make a decent partner for mages.<br>
Just sit back and heal the pet with CH and nuke as mana allows and stack the MoR with damage shield makes for nice added damage.<br>
<br>
Enchanter makes for nice partnering with mage.<br>
They can slow the mob and stun the mob to mitigate the damage output and therefor lessen the amout of damage the pet takes. Also a rich chanter can just rune the pet whie you fight negating the need for a heal. they give added damage thru pet/charmed/or Dire charmed.<br>
<br>
Wizards are so so when teamed with mage.<br>
Wiz/mage combo make for fast kills but sometimes results in downtime cause of the damage taken by the pet,.. however when teamed properly the wizard can create some mean aggro and have the pet chase the kiting wizard's mob and makes for great fast kills plus the pet takes minimal damage.<br>
<br>
Necro mage combo owns at the lower levels (51-60)<br>
Mage summons water pet for backstab and the necro fear kits while mage sends pet and nukes.<br>
<br>
these are prolly the best combos for mages IMHO..<br>
