<br>
the wizard really shines the higher level they get. wizards are definitly designed for the high end raid content of eq were fast damage , big nukes help.<br>
but wizards can't solo that great until they get snare, then quad kiting allows wizards to level pretty fast.<br>
<br>
mages get a nice pet that allows they to solo easily to 60. i decided to play a mage because i was tired of running &quot;away&quot; from mobs, kiting with my wizard. mages are better suited for dungeon crawls and fighting in tight spaces, while a wizard always needs rom to move to kill. a mage can simply sent pet and sit down.<br>
<br>
i would play both classes then decide which you prefer. for exp groups and exploring, i prefer to play my mage. for raids i play my wizard.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral>General</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.101<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href="http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html">JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

